  - key: subtitle.forest_warning
    english: Do not enter the forest after sundown.
    indonesian: Jangan masuk hutan setelah matahari turun.
  - key: subtitle.ancient_script_seen
    english: These symbols... I saw them near the forest.
    indonesian: Simbol ini... pernah kulihat di dekat hutan.
  - key: subtitle.player_first_see_banaspati
    english: What is that fire...?
    indonesian: Api apa itu...?
  - key: subtitle.player_first_see_banaspati_2
    english: That thing is alive.
    indonesian: Benda itu hidup.
  - key: subtitle.player_first_see_banaspati_3
    english: No... that is not normal.
    indonesian: Tidak... itu tidak normal.
  - key: subtitle.player_chased
    english: It saw me. I have to run.
    indonesian: Dia melihatku. Aku harus lari.
  - key: subtitle.player_chased_2
    english: Damn it, it is coming.
    indonesian: Sial, dia mendekat.
  - key: subtitle.player_chased_3
    english: Fuck, run. Run!
    indonesian: Anjing, lari. Lari!
  - key: subtitle.player_chased_4
    english: Do not look back. Just run.
    indonesian: Jangan lihat belakang. Lari saja.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit
    english: The heat is burning through me.
    indonesian: Panasnya membakar tubuhku.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_2
    english: Damn it, that heat hurts.
    indonesian: Sial, panasnya sakit.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_3
    english: Fuck, my skin is burning.
    indonesian: Anjing, kulitku terbakar.
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_before_seeing_banaspati
    english: Something is burning my body...
    indonesian: Ada sesuatu yang membakar tubuhku...
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_before_seeing_banaspati_2
    english: What the hell is burning me...?
    indonesian: Apa yang membakarku...?
  - key: subtitle.player_burn_hit_before_seeing_banaspati_3
    english: The air is burning my skin.
    indonesian: Udaranya membakar kulitku.
  - key: subtitle.player_burning_attack_hit
    english: This fire is pulling me in.
    indonesian: Api ini menarikku masuk.
  - key: subtitle.player_burning_attack_hit_2
    english: Fuck, it is dragging me.
    indonesian: Anjing, dia menyeretku.
  - key: subtitle.player_burning_attack_hit_3
    english: I cannot break free.
    indonesian: Aku tidak bisa lepas.
  - key: subtitle.player_low_stamina_chased
    english: I cannot keep running like this.
    indonesian: Aku tidak bisa terus berlari seperti ini.
  - key: subtitle.player_low_stamina_chased_2
    english: My legs are giving up.
    indonesian: Kakiku mulai menyerah.
  - key: subtitle.player_low_stamina_chased_3
    english: Damn it, I need air.
    indonesian: Sial, aku butuh napas.
  - key: subtitle.player_death_burn
    english: My body... is burning.
    indonesian: Tubuhku... terbakar.
  - key: subtitle.player_death_burning_attack
    english: It is dragging me into the fire.
    indonesian: Dia menyeretku ke dalam api.
  - key: subtitle.player_death_chase
    english: The fire... is lifting me.
    indonesian: Api itu... mengangkatku.
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_short
    english: Aaaa....
    indonesian: Aaaa....
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_final_large
    english: AAAAA......
    indonesian: AAAAA......
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_cutoff
    english: A....
    indonesian: A....
  - key: subtitle.player_scream_air_burn
    english: AAAAAaaaaaa...........
    indonesian: AAAAAaaaaaa...........
  - key: villager_01.name
    english: "Pak Wiryo"
    indonesian: "Pak Wiryo"
  - key: villager_01.occupation
    english: "Farmer"
    indonesian: "Petani"
  - key: villager_01.description
    english: "An experienced farmer who treats Banaspati as an inherited warning, not a witnessed fact."
    indonesian: "Petani berpengalaman yang menganggap Banaspati sebagai peringatan warisan, bukan fakta yang pernah disaksikannya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.1
    english: "You work close to the forest boundary. Have you ever seen anything burning in there?"
    indonesian: "Bapak bekerja dekat batas hutan. Pernah melihat sesuatu yang terbakar di sana?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.2
    english: "Never. In thirty years I have seen lightning, brush fires, and frightened travelers. Nothing more."
    indonesian: "Tidak pernah. Selama tiga puluh tahun aku hanya melihat petir, kebakaran semak, dan pendatang yang ketakutan. Tidak lebih."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.3
    english: "Then why do people here mention Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Lalu kenapa orang-orang di sini menyebut Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.4
    english: "An old tale used to make children come home before dark. At least, that is what I tell myself."
    indonesian: "Cerita orang tua agar anak-anak pulang sebelum gelap. Setidaknya, itulah yang selalu kukatakan pada diriku sendiri."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.5
    english: "You do not sound completely certain."
    indonesian: "Bapak terdengar tidak sepenuhnya yakin."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.first.6
    english: "I am certain the fields need water. For forest stories, ask someone old enough to remember when that name was still whispered."
    indonesian: "Aku yakin sawah membutuhkan air. Untuk cerita hutan, tanyalah kepada orang yang cukup tua untuk mengingat saat nama itu masih dibisikkan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.repeat.1
    english: "So you have never seen it?"
    indonesian: "Jadi Bapak benar-benar tidak pernah melihatnya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.repeat.2
    english: "Never, and I hope it stays that way."
    indonesian: "Tidak pernah, dan semoga tetap begitu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.repeat.3
    english: "Who should I ask?"
    indonesian: "Siapa yang sebaiknya kutanya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_01.repeat.4
    english: "Pak Darma will point you to the right people. Do not mistake a story for proof."
    indonesian: "Pak Darma akan menunjukkan orang yang tepat. Jangan menyamakan cerita dengan bukti."
  - key: villager_02.name
    english: "Bu Sari"
    indonesian: "Bu Sari"
  - key: villager_02.occupation
    english: "Traditional Healer"
    indonesian: "Tabib"
  - key: villager_02.description
    english: "The village healer, careful to separate symptoms she can treat from stories she cannot prove."
    indonesian: "Tabib desa yang berhati-hati membedakan gejala yang dapat diobati dari cerita yang tidak dapat dibuktikan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.1
    english: "Are you the healer in this village?"
    indonesian: "Apakah Ibu tabib di desa ini?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.2
    english: "Yes. I treat fever, wounds, poison, and difficult births. Not curses."
    indonesian: "Ya. Aku menangani demam, luka, racun, dan persalinan sulit. Bukan kutukan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.3
    english: "Have you treated anyone who claimed Banaspati burned them?"
    indonesian: "Pernahkah Ibu merawat orang yang mengaku dibakar Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.4
    english: "I once treated a wood gatherer whose skin was cold while his breath felt too hot. He had no burn marks."
    indonesian: "Aku pernah merawat pencari kayu yang kulitnya dingin sementara napasnya terasa terlalu panas. Tidak ada bekas luka bakar."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.5
    english: "What caused it?"
    indonesian: "Apa penyebabnya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.6
    english: "Dehydration, fear, perhaps a plant. The older women called it invisible fire."
    indonesian: "Dehidrasi, ketakutan, mungkin tumbuhan tertentu. Para perempuan tua menyebutnya api tak terlihat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.7
    english: "Which explanation do you believe?"
    indonesian: "Penjelasan mana yang Ibu percaya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.first.8
    english: "I believe symptoms I can examine. A name can wait until it leaves evidence."
    indonesian: "Aku percaya pada gejala yang dapat kuperiksa. Sebuah nama bisa menunggu sampai meninggalkan bukti."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.repeat.1
    english: "So the invisible fire was only fever?"
    indonesian: "Jadi api tak terlihat itu hanya demam?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.repeat.2
    english: "I said it could be fever. Certainty is not part of my medicine."
    indonesian: "Aku bilang itu bisa saja demam. Kepastian bukan bagian dari obatku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.repeat.3
    english: "Who might know more?"
    indonesian: "Siapa yang mungkin tahu lebih banyak?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_02.repeat.4
    english: "Ki Surya knows memories, Seno knows a story, and I know how to treat a living patient."
    indonesian: "Ki Surya mengenal ingatan, Seno mengenal sebuah cerita, dan aku tahu cara merawat orang yang masih hidup."
  - key: villager_03.name
    english: "Pak Darma"
    indonesian: "Pak Darma"
  - key: villager_03.occupation
    english: "Village Head"
    indonesian: "Kepala Desa"
  - key: villager_03.description
    english: "The village head who directs visitors to the right residents and safeguards the old records."
    indonesian: "Kepala desa yang mengarahkan pendatang kepada warga yang tepat dan menjaga catatan lama."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.1
    english: "Are you Pak Darma, the village head?"
    indonesian: "Apakah Bapak Pak Darma, kepala desa di sini?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.2
    english: "I am. Tell me what your team needs before you wander from door to door."
    indonesian: "Benar. Katakan apa yang timmu butuhkan sebelum kalian berkeliling dari rumah ke rumah."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.3
    english: "We are investigating an old account of a fire creature in Leuweng Sancang. Who knows the forest best?"
    indonesian: "Kami menyelidiki catatan lama tentang makhluk api di Leuweng Sancang. Siapa yang paling mengenal hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.4
    english: "No one here can honestly claim to know the whole forest, and no living villager has proof of such a creature."
    indonesian: "Tidak seorang pun di sini dapat mengaku mengenal seluruh hutan, dan tidak ada warga yang masih hidup memiliki bukti tentang makhluk semacam itu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.5
    english: "But some people enter it often, correct?"
    indonesian: "Tapi ada orang yang sering masuk ke sana, bukan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.6
    english: "Seno cuts wood near its inner paths, and Bima knows the hunting trails. Ask Pak Hasan about the river and the route south."
    indonesian: "Seno menebang kayu di dekat jalur dalam, dan Bima mengenal jalur berburu. Tanyakan sungai dan arah selatan kepada Pak Hasan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.7
    english: "Who should I see about herbs or injuries?"
    indonesian: "Siapa yang harus kutemui untuk tumbuhan obat atau luka?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.8
    english: "Bu Sari is our healer. Ratri knows the flowers, and Wulan knows the springs and clean water."
    indonesian: "Bu Sari adalah tabib kami. Ratri mengenal bunga-bunga, dan Wulan mengetahui mata air serta sumber air bersih."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.9
    english: "What if we need livestock or eggs?"
    indonesian: "Bagaimana jika kami membutuhkan ternak atau telur?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.10
    english: "See Bu Marni. She knows every animal in the village and notices quickly when something disturbs them."
    indonesian: "Temui Bu Marni. Ia mengenal setiap ternak di desa dan cepat menyadari jika ada sesuatu yang mengganggu mereka."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.11
    english: "And provisions or incense?"
    indonesian: "Lalu untuk perbekalan atau kemenyan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.12
    english: "Yuni sells general supplies. Pak Jaya knows benzoin and incense, although his stories are better than his guarantees."
    indonesian: "Yuni menjual kebutuhan umum. Pak Jaya memahami benzoin dan kemenyan, walau ceritanya lebih meyakinkan daripada jaminannya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.13
    english: "Who knows the oldest tales about Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Siapa yang mengetahui cerita tertua tentang Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.14
    english: "Ki Surya remembers what the previous generation whispered. Mbah Karto collects the different versions, but stories are not evidence."
    indonesian: "Ki Surya mengingat apa yang dibisikkan generasi sebelumnya. Mbah Karto mengumpulkan berbagai versinya, tetapi cerita bukanlah bukti."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.15
    english: "What about the old writing in the records?"
    indonesian: "Bagaimana dengan tulisan kuno dalam catatan itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.16
    english: "Dewi studies its patterns. A comparison sheet and copies of the oldest documents are kept in my house."
    indonesian: "Dewi mempelajari polanya. Lembar perbandingan dan salinan dokumen tertua disimpan di rumahku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.17
    english: "Do you believe any of this?"
    indonesian: "Apakah Bapak percaya semua ini?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.first.18
    english: "My duty is to guide living people, not certify the fears of the dead. Speak to them and decide for yourself."
    indonesian: "Tugasku adalah mengarahkan orang yang masih hidup, bukan mengesahkan ketakutan mereka yang telah mati. Bicaralah dengan mereka dan putuskan sendiri."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.1
    english: "Who should I ask about the forest again?"
    indonesian: "Siapa lagi yang harus kutanya tentang hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.2
    english: "Seno and Bima for the land, Pak Hasan for the river. None of them claims to know all of it."
    indonesian: "Seno dan Bima untuk jalur darat, Pak Hasan untuk sungai. Tidak satu pun mengaku mengenal semuanya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.3
    english: "And if we encounter strange heat?"
    indonesian: "Dan jika kami mengalami panas yang aneh?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.4
    english: "See Bu Sari first, then Ki Surya if medicine leaves questions unanswered."
    indonesian: "Temui Bu Sari lebih dahulu, lalu Ki Surya jika pengobatan masih menyisakan pertanyaan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.5
    english: "What about the old records?"
    indonesian: "Bagaimana dengan catatan lama itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_03.repeat.6
    english: "Speak with Dewi, then return to my house."
    indonesian: "Bicaralah dengan Dewi, lalu kembali ke rumahku."
  - key: villager_04.name
    english: "Ratri"
    indonesian: "Ratri"
  - key: villager_04.occupation
    english: "Flower Gatherer"
    indonesian: "Pemetik Bunga"
  - key: villager_04.description
    english: "A flower gatherer who stays within hearing distance of the village and distrusts inherited forest tales."
    indonesian: "Pemetik bunga yang selalu berada dalam jarak dengar desa dan tidak mudah percaya pada cerita hutan warisan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.1
    english: "You gather flowers near Sancang?"
    indonesian: "Kau memetik bunga di dekat Sancang?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.2
    english: "Only where I can still hear the village. The deeper blooms can keep their secrets."
    indonesian: "Hanya di tempat aku masih bisa mendengar suara desa. Bunga yang lebih dalam boleh menyimpan rahasianya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.3
    english: "Because of Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Karena Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.4
    english: "Because people get lost. My grandmother used that name for every red light beyond the trees."
    indonesian: "Karena orang bisa tersesat. Nenekku memakai nama itu untuk setiap cahaya merah di balik pepohonan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.5
    english: "Did she ever see it?"
    indonesian: "Apa nenekmu pernah melihatnya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.first.6
    english: "She only knew stories from her mother. Around here, every generation inherits a warning and none inherits proof."
    indonesian: "Ia hanya mengetahui cerita dari ibunya. Di sini, setiap generasi mewarisi peringatan, tetapi tidak ada yang mewarisi bukti."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.repeat.1
    english: "You really never go deeper?"
    indonesian: "Kau benar-benar tidak pernah masuk lebih dalam?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.repeat.2
    english: "Not alone, and never after the village sounds fade."
    indonesian: "Tidak sendirian, dan tidak pernah setelah suara desa menghilang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.repeat.3
    english: "Because of the old story?"
    indonesian: "Karena cerita lama itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_04.repeat.4
    english: "Because a real ravine can kill me before an imaginary fire gets the chance."
    indonesian: "Karena jurang yang nyata dapat membunuhku sebelum api khayalan mendapat kesempatan."
  - key: villager_05.name
    english: "Pak Jaya"
    indonesian: "Pak Jaya"
  - key: villager_05.occupation
    english: "Incense Trader"
    indonesian: "Pedagang Kemenyan"
  - key: villager_05.description
    english: "A benzoin and incense trader who has heard many claims but witnessed none of them."
    indonesian: "Pedagang benzoin dan kemenyan yang telah mendengar banyak pengakuan tetapi tidak pernah menyaksikannya sendiri."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.1
    english: "Is this incense meant for old rituals?"
    indonesian: "Apakah kemenyan ini digunakan untuk ritual lama?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.2
    english: "It is meant to smell good, repel insects, and earn me money. Rituals are what buyers add to it."
    indonesian: "Kemenyan ini dibuat agar harum, mengusir serangga, dan memberiku penghasilan. Ritual adalah tambahan dari para pembeli."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.3
    english: "Some people connect its smoke to Banaspati."
    indonesian: "Sebagian orang menghubungkan asapnya dengan Banaspati."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.4
    english: "Old customers say smoke carries prayers. Others say it only tells mosquitoes where not to land."
    indonesian: "Pelanggan tua bilang asap membawa doa. Yang lain bilang asap hanya memberi tahu nyamuk tempat yang tidak boleh didatangi."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.5
    english: "Have you ever seen the creature?"
    indonesian: "Apa Bapak pernah melihat makhluk itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.first.6
    english: "Never. I have only watched a rumor become more expensive with every retelling."
    indonesian: "Tidak pernah. Aku hanya menyaksikan sebuah rumor menjadi semakin mahal setiap kali diceritakan ulang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.repeat.1
    english: "So the incense has no mystical power?"
    indonesian: "Jadi kemenyan ini tidak memiliki kekuatan gaib?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.repeat.2
    english: "It has fragrance, smoke, and whatever meaning you bring to it."
    indonesian: "Ia memiliki aroma, asap, dan makna apa pun yang kau berikan kepadanya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.repeat.3
    english: "And Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Lalu Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_05.repeat.4
    english: "Ask an elder. I trade resin, not certainty."
    indonesian: "Tanyakan kepada sesepuh. Aku menjual getah, bukan kepastian."
  - key: villager_06.name
    english: "Bu Marni"
    indonesian: "Bu Marni"
  - key: villager_06.occupation
    english: "Livestock Farmer"
    indonesian: "Peternak"
  - key: villager_06.description
    english: "A livestock farmer who trusts animal tracks more than supernatural explanations."
    indonesian: "Peternak yang lebih mempercayai jejak hewan daripada penjelasan gaib."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.1
    english: "Do your animals ever become restless near the forest?"
    indonesian: "Apakah ternak Ibu pernah gelisah di dekat hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.2
    english: "Goats fear boars, chickens fear thunder, and both fear unfamiliar people."
    indonesian: "Kambing takut babi hutan, ayam takut petir, dan keduanya takut orang asing."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.3
    english: "Do they react to Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa mereka bereaksi terhadap Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.4
    english: "Older people blamed unseen fire whenever the chickens refused to sleep."
    indonesian: "Orang-orang tua menyalahkan api tak terlihat setiap kali ayam tidak mau tidur."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.5
    english: "Have you ever found evidence of it?"
    indonesian: "Apa Ibu pernah menemukan buktinya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.first.6
    english: "Tracks, feathers, broken fences, yes. Nothing shaped like a floating flame."
    indonesian: "Jejak, bulu, dan pagar rusak, ya. Tidak ada yang berbentuk api melayang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.repeat.1
    english: "So the animals have never sensed it?"
    indonesian: "Jadi ternak tidak pernah merasakannya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.repeat.2
    english: "Animals cannot explain what frightened them. People are too eager to explain it for them."
    indonesian: "Hewan tidak dapat menjelaskan apa yang menakuti mereka. Manusia terlalu cepat menjelaskannya untuk mereka."
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.repeat.3
    english: "Who knows the old animal stories?"
    indonesian: "Siapa yang mengetahui cerita lama tentang ternak?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_06.repeat.4
    english: "Ki Surya remembers them. I keep the animals alive."
    indonesian: "Ki Surya mengingatnya. Aku menjaga ternak tetap hidup."
  - key: villager_07.name
    english: "Ki Surya"
    indonesian: "Ki Surya"
  - key: villager_07.occupation
    english: "Village Elder"
    indonesian: "Sesepuh Desa"
  - key: villager_07.description
    english: "The only villager with a possible sighting, though he distrusts his memory and blames tobacco as readily as folklore."
    indonesian: "Satu-satunya warga yang mungkin pernah melihatnya, meski ia meragukan ingatannya dan sama mudahnya menyalahkan tembakau maupun cerita rakyat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.1
    english: "Ki Surya, Pak Darma said you remember the oldest stories."
    indonesian: "Ki Surya, Pak Darma bilang Ki mengingat cerita-cerita tertua."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.2
    english: "Remembering a story does not make it true."
    indonesian: "Mengingat sebuah cerita tidak membuatnya menjadi kenyataan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.3
    english: "Have you ever seen what they call Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa Ki pernah melihat sesuatu yang mereka sebut Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.4
    english: "Once, perhaps. Or I saw dusk through too much tobacco smoke."
    indonesian: "Mungkin sekali. Atau aku hanya melihat senja melalui terlalu banyak asap tembakau."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.5
    english: "Tell me what happened."
    indonesian: "Ceritakan apa yang terjadi."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.6
    english: "More than forty years ago, I searched for a missing goat along the river path after sunset."
    indonesian: "Lebih dari empat puluh tahun lalu, aku mencari kambing yang hilang di jalur sungai setelah matahari terbenam."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.7
    english: "The ground was wet from rain, but the air ahead became dry enough to sting my throat."
    indonesian: "Tanah masih basah oleh hujan, tetapi udara di depanku menjadi begitu kering hingga menusuk tenggorokan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.8
    english: "Between two trees hung a round red light, lower than the branches and higher than any campfire."
    indonesian: "Di antara dua pohon tergantung cahaya merah bulat, lebih rendah dari ranting tetapi lebih tinggi dari api unggun mana pun."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.9
    english: "Was someone carrying it?"
    indonesian: "Apa ada seseorang yang membawanya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.10
    english: "I saw no hand, rope, or body. Only fire folded around a pale center."
    indonesian: "Aku tidak melihat tangan, tali, ataupun tubuh. Hanya api yang melipat mengelilingi inti pucat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.11
    english: "There was no smoke. The shadows leaned toward it, although the last sunlight came from behind me."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada asap. Bayangan-bayangan condong ke arahnya, padahal sisa cahaya senja datang dari belakangku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.12
    english: "Did it approach you?"
    indonesian: "Apa benda itu mendekati Ki?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.13
    english: "It turned. A round thing should have no face, yet I knew the moment it looked at me."
    indonesian: "Benda itu berbalik. Sesuatu yang bulat seharusnya tidak memiliki wajah, tetapi aku tahu saat ia menatapku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.14
    english: "My tobacco tasted bitter. Warmth rose in my chest, and the light vanished when I blinked."
    indonesian: "Tembakauku terasa pahit. Kehangatan naik di dalam dada, lalu cahaya itu lenyap ketika aku berkedip."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.15
    english: "Why did you not tell anyone?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa Ki tidak menceritakannya kepada siapa pun?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.16
    english: "I did. They laughed and said a young fool had finally smoked enough to meet his own smoke."
    indonesian: "Aku menceritakannya. Mereka tertawa dan bilang seorang pemuda bodoh akhirnya mengisap cukup banyak tembakau untuk bertemu asapnya sendiri."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.17
    english: "So you doubt what you saw?"
    indonesian: "Jadi Ki meragukan apa yang Ki lihat?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.18
    english: "Belief is too large a word for one frightened glance."
    indonesian: "Kepercayaan adalah kata yang terlalu besar untuk satu tatapan ketakutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.19
    english: "I only know I never walked that path at dusk again, and the goat returned alone the next morning."
    indonesian: "Aku hanya tahu sejak itu aku tidak pernah melewati jalur tersebut saat senja, dan kambing itu pulang sendiri keesokan paginya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.20
    english: "Did the light leave anything behind?"
    indonesian: "Apa cahaya itu meninggalkan sesuatu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.21
    english: "Nothing I could prove. Listen to my memory, but do not mistake it for evidence."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada yang dapat kubuktikan. Dengarkan ingatanku, tetapi jangan menganggapnya sebagai bukti."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.first.22
    english: "For the name Banaspati, ask Seno. His grandfather's story is older than my sight."
    indonesian: "Untuk nama Banaspati, tanyalah kepada Seno. Cerita kakeknya lebih tua daripada penglihatanku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.1
    english: "Was it only tobacco smoke?"
    indonesian: "Apa itu hanya asap tembakau?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.2
    english: "Perhaps. Tobacco has taken the blame for worse memories."
    indonesian: "Mungkin. Tembakau pernah disalahkan atas ingatan yang jauh lebih buruk."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.3
    english: "Yet you still avoid that path?"
    indonesian: "Tapi Ki masih menghindari jalur itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.4
    english: "Doubt does not erase fear."
    indonesian: "Keraguan tidak menghapus ketakutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.5
    english: "Did Seno's grandfather see the same thing?"
    indonesian: "Apa kakek Seno melihat hal yang sama?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_07.repeat.6
    english: "I do not know. That unanswered part is what has kept the story alive."
    indonesian: "Aku tidak tahu. Bagian yang tidak terjawab itulah yang membuat ceritanya tetap hidup."
  - key: villager_08.name
    english: "Wulan"
    indonesian: "Wulan"
  - key: villager_08.occupation
    english: "Water Carrier"
    indonesian: "Pembawa Air"
  - key: villager_08.description
    english: "A water carrier who knows the local springs and explains strange warmth without invoking monsters."
    indonesian: "Pembawa air yang mengenal mata air setempat dan menjelaskan kehangatan aneh tanpa mengaitkannya dengan monster."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.1
    english: "Do these springs continue into the forest?"
    indonesian: "Apa mata air ini mengalir terus ke dalam hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.2
    english: "Some do. Others disappear underground and return closer to the river."
    indonesian: "Sebagian iya. Yang lain masuk ke bawah tanah dan muncul kembali lebih dekat ke sungai."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.3
    english: "People say the river sometimes turns warm."
    indonesian: "Orang-orang bilang air sungai kadang menjadi hangat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.4
    english: "Sun-heated stone, shallow mud, or a warm spring. Water has many reasons."
    indonesian: "Batu yang dipanaskan matahari, lumpur dangkal, atau mata air hangat. Air punya banyak alasan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.5
    english: "Not Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Bukan karena Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.first.6
    english: "That is a better story than geology, but I have never seen fire in the water."
    indonesian: "Itu cerita yang lebih menarik daripada geologi, tetapi aku tidak pernah melihat api di dalam air."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.repeat.1
    english: "Which water route is safest?"
    indonesian: "Jalur air mana yang paling aman?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.repeat.2
    english: "Ask Pak Hasan. He reads the current better than I do."
    indonesian: "Tanyakan kepada Pak Hasan. Ia membaca arus lebih baik dariku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.repeat.3
    english: "And the warm water?"
    indonesian: "Lalu air yang hangat itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_08.repeat.4
    english: "Test the stone beneath it before blaming an old story."
    indonesian: "Periksa batu di bawahnya sebelum menyalahkan cerita lama."
  - key: villager_09.name
    english: "Bima"
    indonesian: "Bima"
  - key: villager_09.occupation
    english: "Hunter"
    indonesian: "Pemburu"
  - key: villager_09.description
    english: "A hunter familiar with marked trails who considers the forest dangerous without needing a monster."
    indonesian: "Pemburu yang mengenal jalur bertanda dan menganggap hutan sudah berbahaya tanpa memerlukan monster."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.1
    english: "You know the deepest paths in Sancang?"
    indonesian: "Kau mengenal jalur terdalam di Sancang?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.2
    english: "I know the marked hunting trails. Anyone claiming to know the deepest forest is either lying or lost."
    indonesian: "Aku mengenal jalur berburu yang diberi tanda. Siapa pun yang mengaku mengenal hutan terdalam pasti berbohong atau tersesat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.3
    english: "Have you ever seen a ball of fire moving there?"
    indonesian: "Pernahkah kau melihat bola api bergerak di sana?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.4
    english: "I have seen campfires through fog, fireflies in swarms, and frightened eyes turning both into monsters."
    indonesian: "Aku pernah melihat api unggun di balik kabut, kawanan kunang-kunang, dan mata ketakutan yang mengubah keduanya menjadi monster."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.5
    english: "Then why do you leave before dark?"
    indonesian: "Lalu kenapa kau selalu keluar sebelum gelap?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.first.6
    english: "Cliffs, boars, and human traps are real. I do not need Banaspati to respect the night."
    indonesian: "Jurang, babi hutan, dan jerat manusia itu nyata. Aku tidak membutuhkan Banaspati untuk menghormati malam."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.repeat.1
    english: "No unexplained light at all?"
    indonesian: "Tidak ada cahaya yang tidak dapat dijelaskan sama sekali?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.repeat.2
    english: "None that stayed unexplained after I approached it."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada yang tetap tidak dapat dijelaskan setelah kudekati."
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.repeat.3
    english: "Would you enter alone at night?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau mau masuk sendirian pada malam hari?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_09.repeat.4
    english: "No. Skepticism does not make darkness safe."
    indonesian: "Tidak. Keraguan tidak membuat kegelapan menjadi aman."
  - key: villager_10.name
    english: "Seno"
    indonesian: "Seno"
  - key: villager_10.occupation
    english: "Woodcutter"
    indonesian: "Penebang Kayu"
  - key: villager_10.description
    english: "A woodcutter who has never seen Banaspati but carries his grandfather's disturbing account."
    indonesian: "Penebang kayu yang tidak pernah melihat Banaspati tetapi menyimpan kesaksian mengusik dari kakeknya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.1
    english: "Ki Surya said your grandfather gave the forest fire its name."
    indonesian: "Ki Surya bilang kakekmu yang memberi nama pada api di hutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.2
    english: "He gave us a story. Whether that story gave us truth is another matter."
    indonesian: "Ia memberi kami sebuah cerita. Apakah cerita itu juga memberi kebenaran adalah persoalan lain."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.3
    english: "Did you ever see it yourself?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau pernah melihatnya sendiri?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.4
    english: "No. I have cut wood there since I was fifteen and never seen anything that could not be explained."
    indonesian: "Tidak. Aku menebang kayu di sana sejak usia lima belas tahun dan tidak pernah melihat sesuatu yang tidak dapat dijelaskan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.5
    english: "Then tell me exactly what happened to him."
    indonesian: "Kalau begitu, ceritakan dengan jelas apa yang terjadi padanya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.6
    english: "It was near the end of a long dry season, before my father was born."
    indonesian: "Kejadiannya menjelang akhir musim kemarau panjang, sebelum ayahku lahir."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.7
    english: "Grandfather went alone before dawn to mark a fallen rasamala tree beyond the old river bend."
    indonesian: "Kakek pergi sendirian sebelum fajar untuk menandai pohon rasamala tumbang di balik tikungan sungai lama."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.8
    english: "By noon clouds covered the sun. He followed the water home so he would not lose direction."
    indonesian: "Menjelang siang awan menutupi matahari. Ia mengikuti aliran air untuk pulang agar tidak kehilangan arah."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.9
    english: "What was the first strange thing he noticed?"
    indonesian: "Apa keanehan pertama yang ia sadari?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.10
    english: "The insects stopped. Not gradually. Every sound ended at the same moment."
    indonesian: "Serangga-serangga berhenti berbunyi. Bukan perlahan. Semua suara berakhir pada saat yang sama."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.11
    english: "Then came the smell of hot iron. There was no smoke, yet every breath tasted like a burnt coin."
    indonesian: "Lalu muncul bau besi panas. Tidak ada asap, tetapi setiap tarikan napas terasa seperti koin terbakar."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.12
    english: "Across the river, between wet trunks, a light rose without touching the ground."
    indonesian: "Di seberang sungai, di antara batang-batang basah, sebuah cahaya naik tanpa menyentuh tanah."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.13
    english: "What did it look like?"
    indonesian: "Seperti apa wujudnya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.14
    english: "He said it was round, about the size of a human head, but it had no head, eyes, or mouth."
    indonesian: "Katanya benda itu bulat, kira-kira sebesar kepala manusia, tetapi tidak memiliki kepala, mata, ataupun mulut."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.15
    english: "A pale core pulsed inside layers of red fire. Black ash circled it against the wind and never fell."
    indonesian: "Inti pucat berdenyut di dalam lapisan api merah. Abu hitam mengitarinya melawan angin dan tidak pernah jatuh."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.16
    english: "It passed beneath dripping leaves without burning them, then stopped directly opposite him."
    indonesian: "Benda itu melintas di bawah dedaunan yang menetes tanpa membakarnya, lalu berhenti tepat di hadapannya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.17
    english: "How did he know it noticed him?"
    indonesian: "Bagaimana ia tahu benda itu menyadari keberadaannya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.18
    english: "It turned toward him. It had no face, but he felt the certainty of being watched."
    indonesian: "Benda itu berbalik ke arahnya. Ia tidak punya wajah, tetapi Kakek merasakan kepastian bahwa dirinya sedang ditatap."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.19
    english: "The heat did not touch his skin. It began behind his breastbone while his arms remained cold."
    indonesian: "Panasnya tidak menyentuh kulit. Panas itu bermula dari balik tulang dada sementara kedua lengannya tetap dingin."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.20
    english: "His blood felt as if it boiled. Anger, shame, and fear returned at once, scorching his thoughts and heart from within."
    indonesian: "Darahnya terasa mendidih. Amarah, rasa malu, dan ketakutan kembali bersamaan, membakar pikiran dan hatinya dari dalam."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.21
    english: "How did he escape?"
    indonesian: "Bagaimana ia melarikan diri?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.22
    english: "He ran downstream and threw himself into the river. The water cooled his skin, but not the heat inside him."
    indonesian: "Ia berlari mengikuti arus lalu menjatuhkan diri ke sungai. Air mendinginkan kulitnya, tetapi tidak panas di dalam tubuhnya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.23
    english: "The light followed between the trees without a footstep. After that, his memory went dark."
    indonesian: "Cahaya itu mengikuti di antara pepohonan tanpa suara langkah. Setelah itu, ingatannya menjadi gelap."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.24
    english: "Two resin gatherers found him before dawn, unconscious beside the shallow bend with one arm still in the water."
    indonesian: "Dua pencari getah menemukannya sebelum fajar, tidak sadarkan diri di dekat tikungan dangkal dengan satu lengan masih berada di dalam air."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.25
    english: "Was he burned?"
    indonesian: "Apa tubuhnya terbakar?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.26
    english: "His skin had no wound. His clothes were wet and cold, but his breath was fever-hot. Only his axe handle was black where he had gripped it."
    indonesian: "Kulitnya tidak terluka. Pakaiannya basah dan dingin, tetapi napasnya sepanas demam. Hanya gagang kapaknya yang menghitam tepat di tempat ia menggenggamnya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.27
    english: "For three days his fever came and went. Every time he woke, he repeated one word: Banaspati."
    indonesian: "Selama tiga hari demamnya datang dan pergi. Setiap kali terbangun, ia mengulang satu kata: Banaspati."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.28
    english: "Did he say where that name came from?"
    indonesian: "Apa ia mengatakan dari mana nama itu berasal?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.29
    english: "Never. He could not say whether the thing spoke it or the word appeared inside his mind. From then on, the wandering fire had a name."
    indonesian: "Tidak pernah. Ia tidak dapat mengatakan apakah benda itu mengucapkannya atau kata itu muncul di dalam pikirannya. Sejak saat itu, api pengembara memiliki nama."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.30
    english: "Did the villagers believe him?"
    indonesian: "Apa warga desa mempercayainya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.31
    english: "No. They blamed swamp gas, bad water, or madness. Children mocked him until he stopped speaking and never crossed that river bend again."
    indonesian: "Tidak. Mereka menyalahkan gas rawa, air buruk, atau kegilaan. Anak-anak mengejeknya sampai ia berhenti bercerita dan tidak pernah lagi melintasi tikungan sungai itu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.first.32
    english: "I believe my grandfather was terrified, not that his explanation was true. But if the forest falls silent and the air tastes of iron, turn back before you decide he was mad."
    indonesian: "Aku percaya kakekku benar-benar ketakutan, bukan berarti penjelasannya pasti benar. Tetapi jika hutan mendadak sunyi dan udara terasa seperti besi, berbaliklah sebelum kau memutuskan bahwa ia gila."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.1
    english: "Do you believe your grandfather saw Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau percaya kakekmu melihat Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.2
    english: "I believe he saw something and came home broken by it."
    indonesian: "Aku percaya ia melihat sesuatu dan pulang dalam keadaan hancur karenanya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.3
    english: "Did any trace survive?"
    indonesian: "Apa ada jejak yang masih tersisa?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.4
    english: "Nothing that could outlive an argument. Even the black axe handle was eventually burned as firewood."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada yang mampu bertahan dari perdebatan. Bahkan gagang kapak hitam itu akhirnya dibakar sebagai kayu bakar."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.5
    english: "Then why warn me?"
    indonesian: "Lalu kenapa kau memperingatkanku?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.6
    english: "Turning back when the forest goes silent costs you an hour."
    indonesian: "Berbalik saat hutan menjadi sunyi hanya menghabiskan satu jam."
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.7
    english: "And ignoring it?"
    indonesian: "Dan jika mengabaikannya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_10.repeat.8
    english: "If Grandfather was right, you may not have time to regret it."
    indonesian: "Jika Kakek benar, kau mungkin tidak punya waktu untuk menyesal."
  - key: villager_11.name
    english: "Laras"
    indonesian: "Laras"
  - key: villager_11.occupation
    english: "Weaver"
    indonesian: "Penenun"
  - key: villager_11.description
    english: "A weaver who preserves old motifs while remaining skeptical of the tales attached to them."
    indonesian: "Penenun yang melestarikan motif lama tetapi tetap meragukan cerita yang dilekatkan kepadanya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.1
    english: "That red circle appears in several of your cloth patterns."
    indonesian: "Lingkaran merah itu muncul di beberapa pola kainmu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.2
    english: "My grandmother called it the wandering ember. She copied it from an older cloth."
    indonesian: "Nenekku menyebutnya bara pengembara. Ia menyalinnya dari kain yang lebih tua."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.3
    english: "Is it meant to represent Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa itu melambangkan Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.4
    english: "People gave it that meaning later. A pattern survives more easily than the reason it was made."
    indonesian: "Orang-orang memberi makna itu belakangan. Sebuah pola lebih mudah bertahan daripada alasan pola itu dibuat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.5
    english: "Do you believe the story behind it?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau percaya cerita di baliknya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.first.6
    english: "Thread proves that someone had hands. It does not prove those hands saw a monster."
    indonesian: "Benang membuktikan seseorang memiliki tangan. Itu tidak membuktikan tangan tersebut pernah melihat monster."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.repeat.1
    english: "How old is the wandering-ember pattern?"
    indonesian: "Seberapa tua pola bara pengembara itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.repeat.2
    english: "Older than my grandmother, younger than the forest."
    indonesian: "Lebih tua dari nenekku, lebih muda dari hutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.repeat.3
    english: "That is not very precise."
    indonesian: "Itu tidak terlalu pasti."
  - key: dialogue.villager_11.repeat.4
    english: "Neither are most stories that survive by being copied."
    indonesian: "Begitu pula sebagian besar cerita yang bertahan karena disalin."
  - key: villager_12.name
    english: "Tono"
    indonesian: "Tono"
  - key: villager_12.occupation
    english: "Mechanic"
    indonesian: "Mekanik"
  - key: villager_12.description
    english: "The village mechanic who hears travelers' theories while trusting engines and weather instead."
    indonesian: "Mekanik desa yang mendengar teori para pendatang tetapi lebih mempercayai mesin dan cuaca."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.1
    english: "Do travelers often ask you about Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa para pendatang sering menanyakan Banaspati kepadamu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.2
    english: "Tourists ask, researchers argue, and broken vehicles arrive the same either way."
    indonesian: "Wisatawan bertanya, peneliti berdebat, dan kendaraan rusak tetap datang dengan cara yang sama."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.3
    english: "You do not believe the story?"
    indonesian: "Kau tidak percaya ceritanya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.4
    english: "Engines stop because of mud, water, fuel, or neglect. I have never repaired one burned by a floating spirit."
    indonesian: "Mesin mati karena lumpur, air, bahan bakar, atau kelalaian. Aku belum pernah memperbaiki kendaraan yang dibakar roh melayang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.5
    english: "Then why keep vehicles facing the road out?"
    indonesian: "Lalu kenapa kendaraan selalu diarahkan ke jalan keluar?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.first.6
    english: "The road is narrow and rain comes quickly. Practical caution does not require a monster."
    indonesian: "Jalannya sempit dan hujan datang cepat. Kehati-hatian praktis tidak membutuhkan monster."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.repeat.1
    english: "Has anyone brought you a vehicle with strange heat damage?"
    indonesian: "Pernah ada yang membawa kendaraan dengan kerusakan panas aneh?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.repeat.2
    english: "No damage that electricity or an empty radiator could not explain."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada kerusakan yang tidak dapat dijelaskan oleh listrik atau radiator kosong."
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.repeat.3
    english: "So there is no mystery here?"
    indonesian: "Jadi tidak ada misteri di sini?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_12.repeat.4
    english: "There is always a mystery before someone opens the engine."
    indonesian: "Selalu ada misteri sebelum seseorang membuka mesinnya."
  - key: villager_13.name
    english: "Bu Ningsih"
    indonesian: "Bu Ningsih"
  - key: villager_13.occupation
    english: "Cook"
    indonesian: "Juru Masak"
  - key: villager_13.description
    english: "A village cook who treats Banaspati as an old fireside warning rather than a living threat."
    indonesian: "Juru masak desa yang menganggap Banaspati sebagai peringatan lama di dekat perapian, bukan ancaman hidup."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.1
    english: "Did your parents tell stories about Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa orang tua Ibu menceritakan Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.2
    english: "Only when the cooking fire was low and children refused to sleep."
    indonesian: "Hanya saat api tungku mengecil dan anak-anak tidak mau tidur."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.3
    english: "Did anything like it ever happen here?"
    indonesian: "Apa sesuatu seperti itu pernah terjadi di sini?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.4
    english: "I have burned rice, cloth, and one very expensive pot. No fire ever chased me afterward."
    indonesian: "Aku pernah menghanguskan nasi, kain, dan satu panci yang sangat mahal. Tidak ada api yang mengejarku setelahnya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.5
    english: "Then why do people sound uneasy when I mention the name?"
    indonesian: "Lalu kenapa orang-orang terdengar gelisah saat aku menyebut namanya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.first.6
    english: "Because people laugh at old stories in daylight and remember every word after dark."
    indonesian: "Karena orang menertawakan cerita lama di siang hari dan mengingat setiap katanya setelah gelap."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.repeat.1
    english: "You truly think it is only a bedtime story?"
    indonesian: "Ibu benar-benar menganggapnya hanya cerita pengantar tidur?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.repeat.2
    english: "That is all it has ever been in my kitchen."
    indonesian: "Hanya itu bentuknya di dapurku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.repeat.3
    english: "And outside the kitchen?"
    indonesian: "Lalu di luar dapur?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_13.repeat.4
    english: "Outside, ask someone who enjoys cold food and long arguments."
    indonesian: "Di luar sana, tanyakan kepada orang yang menyukai makanan dingin dan perdebatan panjang."
  - key: villager_14.name
    english: "Agus"
    indonesian: "Agus"
  - key: villager_14.occupation
    english: "Night Guard"
    indonesian: "Penjaga Malam"
  - key: villager_14.description
    english: "The night guard who watches for ordinary dangers and treats Banaspati as an old explanation for false alarms."
    indonesian: "Penjaga malam yang mengawasi bahaya biasa dan menganggap Banaspati sebagai penjelasan lama untuk alarm palsu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.1
    english: "What do you watch for at night?"
    indonesian: "Apa yang kau awasi pada malam hari?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.2
    english: "Thieves, boars, house fires, and people who forget where they left their lanterns."
    indonesian: "Pencuri, babi hutan, kebakaran rumah, dan orang yang lupa menaruh lentera."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.3
    english: "Have you ever seen a light moving on its own?"
    indonesian: "Pernahkah kau melihat cahaya bergerak sendiri?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.4
    english: "Lanterns in fog, fireflies, and drunk men walking crookedly. All had ordinary owners by morning."
    indonesian: "Lentera di dalam kabut, kunang-kunang, dan orang mabuk yang berjalan sempoyongan. Semuanya memiliki pemilik biasa saat pagi tiba."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.5
    english: "Why does the village still keep an old warning bell?"
    indonesian: "Kenapa desa masih menyimpan lonceng peringatan lama?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.first.6
    english: "It warns of real fire. Banaspati was added to the explanation long after the bell was hung."
    indonesian: "Lonceng itu memperingatkan kebakaran sungguhan. Banaspati baru ditambahkan ke dalam penjelasan lama setelah lonceng dipasang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.repeat.1
    english: "No mysterious light during your watch?"
    indonesian: "Tidak ada cahaya misterius selama kau berjaga?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.repeat.2
    english: "None willing to stay mysterious until sunrise."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada yang mau tetap misterius sampai matahari terbit."
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.repeat.3
    english: "Would you follow one into the forest?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau akan mengikuti cahaya ke dalam hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_14.repeat.4
    english: "No. A guard who abandons his post for a rumor is simply a bad guard."
    indonesian: "Tidak. Penjaga yang meninggalkan pos demi rumor hanyalah penjaga yang buruk."
  - key: villager_15.name
    english: "Dewi"
    indonesian: "Dewi"
  - key: villager_15.occupation
    english: "Teacher"
    indonesian: "Guru"
  - key: villager_15.description
    english: "A teacher studying old script who distinguishes written warnings from reliable eyewitness evidence."
    indonesian: "Guru yang mempelajari aksara lama dan membedakan peringatan tertulis dari bukti saksi yang dapat dipercaya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.1
    english: "Can you read the symbols in the old documents?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau dapat membaca simbol dalam dokumen lama?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.2
    english: "Some of them. A comparison sheet is kept in the village head's house."
    indonesian: "Sebagiannya. Lembar perbandingan disimpan di rumah kepala desa."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.3
    english: "Do the documents mention Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa dokumen itu menyebut Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.4
    english: "That name appears only in later notes. The oldest lines are damaged and can be read in several ways."
    indonesian: "Nama itu hanya muncul dalam catatan yang lebih baru. Baris tertua rusak dan dapat dibaca dengan beberapa cara."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.5
    english: "So the writing proves nothing?"
    indonesian: "Jadi tulisan itu tidak membuktikan apa pun?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.first.6
    english: "It proves someone wrote a warning. It does not prove what frightened them."
    indonesian: "Tulisan itu membuktikan seseorang menulis peringatan. Tulisan itu tidak membuktikan apa yang menakuti mereka."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.repeat.1
    english: "The comparison sheet is still in Pak Darma's house?"
    indonesian: "Lembar perbandingan masih ada di rumah Pak Darma?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.repeat.2
    english: "Yes. Study the shapes before judging the translation."
    indonesian: "Ya. Pelajari bentuknya sebelum menilai terjemahannya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.repeat.3
    english: "And the name Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Lalu nama Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_15.repeat.4
    english: "Treat it as a later annotation until stronger evidence says otherwise."
    indonesian: "Anggap itu sebagai catatan tambahan yang lebih baru sampai ada bukti lebih kuat."
  - key: villager_16.name
    english: "Raka"
    indonesian: "Raka"
  - key: villager_16.occupation
    english: "Farmhand"
    indonesian: "Buruh Tani"
  - key: villager_16.description
    english: "A skeptical young farmhand who mocks the old tale but still respects the dangers of getting lost."
    indonesian: "Buruh tani muda yang meragukan cerita lama tetapi tetap menghormati bahaya tersesat."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.1
    english: "Have you ever gone into the forest at night?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau pernah masuk ke hutan pada malam hari?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.2
    english: "Only far enough to prove to my friends that I was not afraid."
    indonesian: "Hanya cukup jauh untuk membuktikan kepada teman-temanku bahwa aku tidak takut."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.3
    english: "Did you see Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau melihat Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.4
    english: "I saw a red light, then found the farmer carrying it while looking for a calf."
    indonesian: "Aku melihat cahaya merah, lalu menemukan petani yang membawanya saat mencari anak sapi."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.5
    english: "Then why did you come back so quickly?"
    indonesian: "Lalu kenapa kau kembali begitu cepat?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.first.6
    english: "Because being lost all night would be humiliating. Not because a fireball knew my name."
    indonesian: "Karena tersesat semalaman akan memalukan. Bukan karena bola api mengetahui namaku."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.repeat.1
    english: "Still certain the story is nonsense?"
    indonesian: "Masih yakin ceritanya tidak masuk akal?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.repeat.2
    english: "Certain enough in daylight."
    indonesian: "Cukup yakin saat siang hari."
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.repeat.3
    english: "And after dark?"
    indonesian: "Lalu setelah gelap?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_16.repeat.4
    english: "After dark I become practical, not superstitious."
    indonesian: "Setelah gelap aku menjadi praktis, bukan percaya takhayul."
  - key: villager_17.name
    english: "Mbah Karto"
    indonesian: "Mbah Karto"
  - key: villager_17.occupation
    english: "Storyteller"
    indonesian: "Pencerita Desa"
  - key: villager_17.description
    english: "A collector of conflicting Banaspati tales who preserves questions without claiming any version is true."
    indonesian: "Pengumpul berbagai cerita Banaspati yang saling bertentangan dan menjaga pertanyaannya tanpa mengaku satu versi sebagai kebenaran."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.1
    english: "You collect stories about Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Mbah mengumpulkan cerita tentang Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.2
    english: "I collect versions. Anyone offering one true version is selling certainty."
    indonesian: "Aku mengumpulkan berbagai versi. Siapa pun yang menawarkan satu versi benar sedang menjual kepastian."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.3
    english: "Where did the name begin?"
    indonesian: "Dari mana nama itu bermula?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.4
    english: "Most people trace it to the night Seno's grandfather was found beside the river. Before that, it was only the wandering fire."
    indonesian: "Kebanyakan orang menelusurinya ke malam saat kakek Seno ditemukan di dekat sungai. Sebelumnya, ia hanya disebut api pengembara."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.5
    english: "What does the oldest version say?"
    indonesian: "Apa isi versi tertua?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.6
    english: "One warns of a fire that chooses what it burns. Another says it is only guilt reflected in the dark."
    indonesian: "Satu versi memperingatkan tentang api yang memilih apa yang dibakarnya. Versi lain bilang itu hanya rasa bersalah yang terpantul dalam gelap."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.7
    english: "Which version do you believe?"
    indonesian: "Versi mana yang Mbah percaya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.8
    english: "Neither. A storyteller preserves questions, not proof."
    indonesian: "Tidak satu pun. Seorang pencerita menjaga pertanyaan, bukan bukti."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.9
    english: "Has anyone besides Ki Surya claimed to see it?"
    indonesian: "Apa ada orang selain Ki Surya yang mengaku melihatnya?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.first.10
    english: "Many claimed it after hearing the tale. That is why one doubtful witness is worth more than a hundred echoes."
    indonesian: "Banyak yang mengaku setelah mendengar ceritanya. Itulah sebabnya satu saksi yang ragu lebih berharga daripada seratus gema."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.repeat.1
    english: "So there is no single true Banaspati story?"
    indonesian: "Jadi tidak ada satu cerita Banaspati yang benar?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.repeat.2
    english: "Not one I can prove."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada yang dapat kubuktikan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.repeat.3
    english: "Why preserve them, then?"
    indonesian: "Lalu kenapa semua itu disimpan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_17.repeat.4
    english: "Because what a village fears can matter even when the fear has no body."
    indonesian: "Karena apa yang ditakuti sebuah desa tetap berarti meski ketakutan itu tidak memiliki tubuh."
  - key: villager_18.name
    english: "Yuni"
    indonesian: "Yuni"
  - key: villager_18.occupation
    english: "Shopkeeper"
    indonesian: "Pemilik Toko"
  - key: villager_18.description
    english: "The general shopkeeper who sells practical expedition supplies rather than supernatural certainty."
    indonesian: "Pemilik toko umum yang menjual perlengkapan ekspedisi praktis, bukan kepastian gaib."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.1
    english: "Do you sell anything meant to protect people from Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Apa kau menjual sesuatu untuk melindungi orang dari Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.2
    english: "I sell rain covers, batteries, rope, food, and medicine. Those protect people from things we can count."
    indonesian: "Aku menjual pelindung hujan, baterai, tali, makanan, dan obat. Benda-benda itu melindungi orang dari hal yang dapat dihitung."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.3
    english: "No charms or special water?"
    indonesian: "Tidak ada jimat atau air khusus?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.4
    english: "If I sold a story in a bottle, visitors would pay more than they pay for clean water."
    indonesian: "Jika aku menjual cerita di dalam botol, pendatang akan membayar lebih mahal daripada untuk air bersih."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.5
    english: "You do not believe the old tale?"
    indonesian: "Kau tidak percaya cerita lama itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.first.6
    english: "I have never seen it. But fear still makes people forget batteries, so I prepare for what fear does."
    indonesian: "Aku tidak pernah melihatnya. Tetapi ketakutan tetap membuat orang lupa membawa baterai, jadi aku bersiap menghadapi akibat ketakutan."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.repeat.1
    english: "What should we take into the forest?"
    indonesian: "Apa yang harus kami bawa ke hutan?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.repeat.2
    english: "Water, light, medicine, rope, and less confidence than you arrived with."
    indonesian: "Air, penerangan, obat, tali, dan rasa percaya diri yang lebih sedikit daripada saat kalian datang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.repeat.3
    english: "Nothing for Banaspati?"
    indonesian: "Tidak ada apa pun untuk Banaspati?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_18.repeat.4
    english: "Nothing with a guarantee printed on it."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada yang memiliki jaminan tertulis."
  - key: villager_19.name
    english: "Pak Hasan"
    indonesian: "Pak Hasan"
  - key: villager_19.occupation
    english: "Fisherman"
    indonesian: "Nelayan"
  - key: villager_19.description
    english: "A fisherman who knows the lower river and the bend where Seno's grandfather was found unconscious."
    indonesian: "Nelayan yang mengenal bagian hilir sungai dan tikungan tempat kakek Seno ditemukan tidak sadarkan diri."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.1
    english: "Do you know the river route into Sancang?"
    indonesian: "Apa Bapak mengenal jalur sungai menuju Sancang?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.2
    english: "Only the lower bends. Farther in, fallen trees and changing currents erase every reliable route."
    indonesian: "Hanya tikungan bagian hilir. Lebih jauh ke dalam, pohon tumbang dan arus yang berubah menghapus setiap jalur yang dapat dipercaya."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.3
    english: "Have you seen strange fire reflected on the water?"
    indonesian: "Pernahkah Bapak melihat api aneh terpantul di air?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.4
    english: "Only lanterns, sunsets, and fishermen exaggerating after a poor catch."
    indonesian: "Hanya lentera, matahari terbenam, dan nelayan yang melebih-lebihkan cerita setelah tangkapan buruk."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.5
    english: "Was Seno's grandfather really found near the river?"
    indonesian: "Apa kakek Seno benar-benar ditemukan di dekat sungai?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.6
    english: "At the old shallow bend, yes. I heard it from my father, who heard it from one of the men who carried him home."
    indonesian: "Di tikungan dangkal lama, ya. Aku mendengarnya dari ayahku, yang mendengar dari salah satu orang yang membawanya pulang."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.7
    english: "Did the river leave any evidence?"
    indonesian: "Apa sungai meninggalkan bukti?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.first.8
    english: "None. It carried the man back alive and kept whatever answer passed through it that night."
    indonesian: "Tidak ada. Sungai mengembalikan orang itu dalam keadaan hidup dan menyimpan jawaban apa pun yang melewatinya malam itu."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.repeat.1
    english: "Can you show me the old shallow bend?"
    indonesian: "Apa Bapak dapat menunjukkan tikungan dangkal lama itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.repeat.2
    english: "I can show you where it used to be. Rivers move, even when stories do not."
    indonesian: "Aku dapat menunjukkan tempatnya dahulu. Sungai berpindah, meski cerita tidak."
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.repeat.3
    english: "And you never saw the fire?"
    indonesian: "Dan Bapak tidak pernah melihat api itu?"
  - key: dialogue.villager_19.repeat.4
    english: "Never. Water has given me enough real dangers."
    indonesian: "Tidak pernah. Air sudah memberiku cukup banyak bahaya nyata."
  - key: speaker.crew_1
    english: Crew 1
    indonesian: Kru 1
  - key: ui.skip
    english: Skip >>
    indonesian: Lewati >>
  - key: speaker.crew_2
    english: Crew 2
    indonesian: Kru 2
  - key: city.opening.01
    english: Let's review the archive once more before we reach the village.
    indonesian: Mari kita periksa arsip itu sekali lagi sebelum kita tiba di desa.
  - key: city.opening.02
    english: The catalog dates it to the final decades of the colonial administration.
    indonesian: Katalog mencatatnya berasal dari dekade terakhir pemerintahan kolonial.
  - key: city.opening.03
    english: What bothers me is that a field report like this survived at all.
    indonesian: Yang menggangguku, laporan lapangan seperti ini bisa bertahan sampai
      sekarang.
  - key: city.opening.04
    english: It was filed as an expedition incident, not as a folktale.
    indonesian: Dokumen itu dicatat sebagai insiden ekspedisi, bukan cerita rakyat.
  - key: city.opening.05
    english: A patrol entered the southern forest after several workers disappeared.
    indonesian: Sebuah patroli memasuki hutan selatan setelah beberapa pekerja menghilang.
  - key: city.opening.06
    english: The official summary blamed wildfire, panic, and poor visibility.
    indonesian: Ringkasan resminya menyalahkan kebakaran hutan, kepanikan, dan jarak
      pandang buruk.
  - key: city.opening.07
    english: But the witness notes describe a fire that moved against the wind.
    indonesian: Tapi catatan saksi menggambarkan api yang bergerak melawan arah angin.
  - key: city.opening.08
    english: It burned selected targets while leaving wet vegetation untouched.
    indonesian: Api itu membakar sasaran tertentu sementara tumbuhan basah tetap
      utuh.
  - key: city.opening.09
    english: That sounds exactly like a story people would tell around a fire.
    indonesian: Itu terdengar persis seperti cerita yang dibawakan di sekitar api
      unggun.
  - key: city.opening.10
    english: Except the accounts came from different soldiers and were written separately.
    indonesian: Kecuali kesaksian itu berasal dari prajurit berbeda dan ditulis terpisah.
  - key: city.opening.11
    english: They disagreed about its shape, but all described unbearable heat.
    indonesian: Mereka berbeda soal bentuknya, tetapi semuanya menggambarkan panas
      tak tertahankan.
  - key: city.opening.12
    english: One survivor wrote that the fire watched them before it attacked.
    indonesian: Seorang penyintas menulis bahwa api itu mengawasi mereka sebelum
      menyerang.
  - key: city.opening.13
    english: The archive also records the settlement's old name, Sancang.
    indonesian: Arsip itu juga mencatat nama lama permukimannya, Sancang.
  - key: city.opening.14
    english: That name no longer appears as a village on modern maps.
    indonesian: Nama itu tidak lagi tercantum sebagai desa pada peta modern.
  - key: city.opening.15
    english: But its directions point south of Garut Regency.
    indonesian: Tapi petunjuk arahnya mengarah ke selatan Kabupaten Garut.
  - key: city.opening.16
    english: Straight toward Sancang Forest.
    indonesian: Tepat menuju Hutan Sancang.
  - key: city.opening.17
    english: People around there call it Leuweung Sancang.
    indonesian: Warga sekitar menyebutnya Leuweung Sancang.
  - key: city.opening.18
    english: A colonial report and local oral history lead to the same forest.
    indonesian: Laporan kolonial dan cerita lisan warga mengarah ke hutan yang sama.
  - key: city.opening.19
    english: Folklore changes as it is passed down. An archive is different evidence.
    indonesian: Cerita rakyat berubah saat diwariskan. Arsip adalah bukti yang berbeda.
  - key: city.opening.20
    english: Still, an old report can contain fear, rumor, and mistakes.
    indonesian: Tetap saja, laporan lama bisa berisi ketakutan, desas-desus, dan
      kekeliruan.
  - key: city.opening.21
    english: That is why we document everything, photographs, temperature, soil,
      and testimony.
    indonesian: Itu sebabnya kita mencatat semuanya, foto, suhu, tanah, dan kesaksian.
  - key: city.opening.22
    english: We stop for supplies, continue to the village, then speak with the residents.
    indonesian: Kita berhenti membeli perlengkapan, lanjut ke desa, lalu bicara dengan
      warga.
  - key: city.opening.23
    english: Do not show them the archive first. We need accounts it has not influenced.
    indonesian: Jangan tunjukkan arsipnya lebih dulu. Kita butuh kesaksian yang tidak
      dipengaruhinya.
  - key: city.opening.24
    english: If their stories match, this may be more than a bedtime tale.
    indonesian: Jika cerita mereka cocok, ini mungkin lebih dari sekadar dongeng
      pengantar tidur.
  - key: ui.yes
    english: Yes
    indonesian: Ya
  - key: ui.no
    english: No
    indonesian: Tidak
  - key: city.pedestrian.occupation.traveler
    english: Traveler
    indonesian: Pelancong
  - key: city.pedestrian.occupation.visitor
    english: Visitor
    indonesian: Pengunjung
  - key: city.pedestrian.occupation.driver
    english: Driver
    indonesian: Pengemudi
  - key: city.pedestrian.description
    english: A traveler stopping at the rest area.
    indonesian: Seorang pelancong yang berhenti di area istirahat.
  - key: city.pedestrian.01.name
    english: Rudi
    indonesian: Rudi
  - key: city.pedestrian.01.line.1
    english: The road ahead looks quiet. I hope it stays that way.
    indonesian: Jalan di depan kelihatannya sepi. Semoga tetap begitu.
  - key: city.pedestrian.01.line.2
    english: I only stopped to stretch my legs and buy a drink.
    indonesian: Saya cuma berhenti untuk meregangkan kaki dan membeli minuman.
  - key: city.pedestrian.01.line.3
    english: Sorry, I am not from around here. You should ask the cashier.
    indonesian: Maaf, saya bukan orang sekitar sini. Coba tanyakan kepada kasir.
  - key: city.pedestrian.02.name
    english: Dini
    indonesian: Dini
  - key: city.pedestrian.02.line.1
    english: This rest area is small, but at least the shop is still open.
    indonesian: Area istirahat ini kecil, tapi setidaknya tokonya masih buka.
  - key: city.pedestrian.02.line.2
    english: The air gets colder surprisingly fast out here.
    indonesian: Udara di sini ternyata cepat sekali menjadi dingin.
  - key: city.pedestrian.02.line.3
    english: Sancang? I have heard the name, but I know nothing about it.
    indonesian: Sancang? Saya pernah mendengar namanya, tapi tidak tahu apa-apa.
  - key: city.pedestrian.03.name
    english: Asep
    indonesian: Asep
  - key: city.pedestrian.03.line.1
    english: Fill up before continuing. There may not be another stop for a while.
    indonesian: Isi perbekalan sebelum lanjut. Mungkin tidak ada tempat berhenti lagi dalam waktu dekat.
  - key: city.pedestrian.03.line.2
    english: I drive this route occasionally, but never deep into the southern forest.
    indonesian: Kadang saya melewati jalur ini, tapi tidak pernah masuk jauh ke hutan selatan.
  - key: city.pedestrian.03.line.3
    english: I do not know any local legends. I am just waiting for my coffee.
    indonesian: Saya tidak tahu legenda setempat. Saya cuma sedang menunggu kopi.
  - key: city.kopdes.cashier.name
    english: Kopdes Cashier
    indonesian: Kasir Kopdes
  - key: city.kopdes.cashier.occupation
    english: Cashier
    indonesian: Kasir
  - key: city.kopdes.cashier.description
    english: The cashier of the cooperative shop at the rest area.
    indonesian: Kasir toko koperasi desa di area istirahat.
  - key: city.kopdes.greeting
    english: Welcome to Kopdes. Are you looking for supplies or directions?
    indonesian: Selamat datang di Kopdes. Mencari perbekalan atau petunjuk jalan?
  - key: city.kopdes.choice.banaspati
    english: Ask about Banaspati
    indonesian: Tanyakan tentang Banaspati
  - key: city.kopdes.choice.reason
    english: Why is Kopdes here?
    indonesian: Kenapa Kopdes ada di sini?
  - key: city.kopdes.choice.forest
    english: Ask about Prabu Siliwangi
    indonesian: Tanyakan tentang Prabu Siliwangi
  - key: city.kopdes.choice.distance
    english: How far is Sancang Forest?
    indonesian: Seberapa jauh Hutan Sancang?
  - key: city.kopdes.choice.price
    english: How much is all of this?
    indonesian: Berapa harga semua ini?
  - key: city.kopdes.choice.leave
    english: End conversation
    indonesian: Akhiri percakapan
  - key: city.kopdes.question.banaspati
    english: Have you ever heard of something called Banaspati?
    indonesian: Pernah mendengar sesuatu yang disebut Banaspati?
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.banaspati.1
    english: Only from old stories. They say it is a living ball of fire that guards the depths of Sancang.
    indonesian: Hanya dari cerita orang tua. Katanya itu bola api hidup yang menjaga pedalaman Sancang.
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.banaspati.2
    english: It supposedly appears to people with bad intentions. I have never seen it, and I would rather keep it that way.
    indonesian: Katanya ia menampakkan diri kepada orang yang berniat buruk. Saya belum pernah melihatnya dan lebih baik tetap begitu.
  - key: city.kopdes.question.reason
    english: Why build a Kopdes in a place this remote?
    indonesian: Kenapa membangun Kopdes di tempat terpencil seperti ini?
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.reason.joke
    english: Perhaps the government needed somewhere to waste money and inflate the budget.
    indonesian: Mungkin pemerintah butuh tempat untuk menghamburkan uang dan me-markup anggaran.
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.reason.real
    english: I am joking. This is being developed as a rest area, so more travelers are expected to stop here.
    indonesian: Saya bercanda. Tempat ini sedang dikembangkan sebagai area istirahat, jadi nanti akan banyak pelancong berhenti di sini.
  - key: city.kopdes.question.forest
    english: Is Sancang Forest connected to the story of Prabu Siliwangi?
    indonesian: Apakah Hutan Sancang berkaitan dengan cerita Prabu Siliwangi?
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.forest.1
    english: The story I heard says Prabu Siliwangi withdrew into that forest after his son, Kian Santang, pursued him and asked him to embrace Islam, but he refused.
    indonesian: Cerita yang saya dengar mengatakan Prabu Siliwangi mengasingkan diri ke hutan itu setelah dikejar putranya, Kian Santang, yang memintanya masuk Islam, tetapi beliau menolak.
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.forest.2
    english: They say he lived in isolation there for years and eventually emerged from the forest alive.
    indonesian: Katanya beliau mengasingkan diri di sana selama bertahun-tahun dan akhirnya keluar dari hutan dengan selamat.
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.forest.3
    english: If Banaspati truly inhabits Sancang, perhaps the king was simply fortunate never to encounter it.
    indonesian: Kalau Banaspati benar-benar menghuni Sancang, mungkin sang raja hanya beruntung tidak pernah bertemu dengannya.
  - key: city.kopdes.question.distance
    english: About how far is the forest from here?
    indonesian: Kira-kira seberapa jauh hutan itu dari sini?
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.distance
    english: Customers say it is roughly twenty kilometers, perhaps three or four hours depending on the road. That is only an estimate.
    indonesian: Kata pelanggan jaraknya sekitar dua puluh kilometer, mungkin tiga sampai empat jam tergantung kondisi jalan. Itu hanya perkiraan.
  - key: city.kopdes.question.price
    english: How much for all these supplies?
    indonesian: Berapa harga semua perbekalan ini?
  - key: city.kopdes.answer.price
    english: The total is one hundred and fifty thousand rupiah. Would you like to take everything?
    indonesian: Totalnya seratus lima puluh ribu rupiah. Jadi ambil semuanya?
  - key: city.kopdes.purchase.yes
    english: All right. I will pack everything for you.
    indonesian: Baik. Akan saya kemas semuanya.
  - key: city.kopdes.purchase.no
    english: No problem. Let me know if you change your mind.
    indonesian: Tidak masalah. Beri tahu saya jika berubah pikiran.
  - key: city.road.01
    english: Is that a fuel station ahead? We should stop there and check our supplies.
    indonesian: Itu stasiun pengisian bahan bakar di depan? Kita singgah di sana dan periksa perbekalan.
  - key: city.road.02
    english: Sancang reminds me of an old legend from the Pajajaran kingdom.
    indonesian: Sancang mengingatkanku pada sebuah legenda lama dari Kerajaan Pajajaran.
  - key: city.road.03
    english: The one about Prabu Siliwangi entering Sancang Forest?
    indonesian: Yang menceritakan Prabu Siliwangi masuk ke Hutan Sancang?
  - key: city.road.04
    english: Yes. One version says he entered the forest but never returned. Some say he vanished there with his followers.
    indonesian: Ya. Salah satu versinya mengatakan beliau masuk ke hutan itu tetapi tidak pernah kembali. Ada yang bilang beliau menghilang bersama para pengikutnya.
  - key: city.road.05
    english: Make a note of it. We will ask whether the people here still know that story.
    indonesian: Catat dulu. Kita tanyakan apakah orang-orang di sini masih mengenal cerita itu.
  - key: city.road.06
    english: Another legend leading to the same forest. That is difficult to ignore.
    indonesian: Legenda lain yang mengarah ke hutan yang sama. Itu sulit untuk diabaikan.
  - key: city.road.07
    english: Interesting, but we verify the archive first.
    indonesian: Menarik, tetapi kita verifikasi arsipnya terlebih dahulu.
  - key: city.road.arrival
    english: Damn, why is there a Kopdes in a place like this?
    indonesian: Anjing, kenapa ada Kopdes di tempat seperti ini?
  - key: city.departure.01
    english: The cashier's story changes our assumption. Prabu Siliwangi reportedly left Sancang alive.
    indonesian: Cerita kasir tadi mengubah dugaan kita. Prabu Siliwangi kabarnya keluar dari Sancang dengan selamat.
  - key: city.departure.02
    english: Then perhaps the king was connected to whatever happened in that forest.
    indonesian: Kalau begitu, mungkin sang raja memang berhubungan dengan sesuatu yang terjadi di hutan itu.
  - key: city.departure.03
    english: Wait. Let me open the archive again. There is a note from the carbon analysis.
    indonesian: Tunggu. Aku buka kembali arsipnya. Ada catatan dari analisis jejak karbon.
  - key: city.departure.04
    english: The scientists dated evidence of a violent struggle to more than six hundred years ago, long before that kingdom existed.
    indonesian: Para ilmuwan memperkirakan jejak pertarungan besar itu berumur lebih dari enam ratus tahun, jauh sebelum kerajaan itu berdiri.
  - key: city.departure.05
    english: Then the two stories may not be connected after all.
    indonesian: Kalau begitu, sepertinya kedua cerita ini memang tidak berhubungan.
  - key: city.departure.06
    english: Or the cashier was right. During his exile, the king may simply never have encountered Banaspati.
    indonesian: Atau kasir itu benar. Selama pengasingannya, sang raja mungkin memang tidak pernah bertemu Banaspati.
  - key: city.departure.07
    english: The research notes say the samples came from several burned areas, not a single patch of soil.
    indonesian: Catatan penelitiannya menyebut sampel diambil dari beberapa area terbakar, bukan hanya satu titik tanah.
  - key: city.departure.08
    english: That makes the event extensive, but carbon dating only proves that something burned there.
    indonesian: Itu membuktikan kejadiannya luas, tetapi penanggalan karbon hanya membuktikan pernah ada sesuatu yang terbakar di sana.
  - key: city.departure.09
    english: The colonial survivors claimed the ashes moved against the wind and followed anyone who tried to escape.
    indonesian: Para penyintas kolonial mengaku abunya bergerak melawan arah angin dan mengikuti siapa pun yang mencoba kabur.
  - key: city.departure.10
    english: That may be why their report called it Ashes That Remember.
    indonesian: Mungkin itu sebabnya laporan mereka menyebutnya Ashes That Remember.
  - key: city.departure.11
    english: Or that phrase was added later by a translator who wanted the report to sound more dramatic.
    indonesian: Atau istilah itu ditambahkan penerjemah belakangan agar laporannya terdengar lebih dramatis.
  - key: city.departure.12
    english: Even so, both the cashier's story and the archive describe fire that acts with intent.
    indonesian: Meski begitu, cerita kasir dan arsip sama-sama menggambarkan api yang bertindak seolah memiliki kehendak.
  - key: city.departure.13
    english: The villagers may tell us whether that detail existed before the colonial expedition arrived.
    indonesian: Warga desa mungkin bisa memastikan apakah bagian cerita itu sudah ada sebelum ekspedisi kolonial datang.
  - key: city.departure.14
    english: We compare their stories, record the route, and leave every conclusion open until we see the forest ourselves.
    indonesian: Kita bandingkan cerita mereka, catat jalurnya, dan jangan simpulkan apa pun sebelum melihat hutannya sendiri.
  - key: ui.loading
    english: Loading...
    indonesian: Memuat...
  - key: village.journey.01
    english: The city is completely behind us now. This is starting to look like real countryside.
    indonesian: Kota sudah benar-benar tertinggal di belakang. Sekarang mulai terlihat suasana pedesaan.
  - key: village.journey.02
    english: The fields are still busy. It feels calmer than the road we just left.
    indonesian: Ladangnya masih ramai. Suasananya terasa lebih tenang daripada jalan yang baru kita lewati.
  - key: village.journey.03
    english: Calm on the surface, perhaps. I keep wondering about Banaspati and the forest beyond this village.
    indonesian: Mungkin hanya terlihat tenang. Aku terus memikirkan Banaspati dan hutan di balik desa ini.
  - key: village.journey.04
    english: Sancang is enormous. Do you think the villagers have ever explored its deeper regions?
    indonesian: Sancang sangat luas. Menurut kalian, apakah warga pernah menelusuri bagian terdalamnya?
  - key: village.journey.05
    english: Hunters or resin collectors may have entered, but that does not mean they mapped the whole forest.
    indonesian: Pemburu atau pencari getah mungkin pernah masuk, tetapi bukan berarti mereka memetakan seluruh hutannya.
  - key: village.journey.06
    english: Then why are there no reliable local records of a creature that supposedly burned an entire expedition?
    indonesian: Lalu kenapa tidak ada catatan warga yang meyakinkan tentang makhluk yang katanya membakar satu ekspedisi?
  - key: village.journey.07
    english: You are beginning to doubt the colonial archive.
    indonesian: Kau mulai meragukan arsip dari masa penjajahan itu.
  - key: village.journey.08
    english: I am questioning its conclusion. The soldiers may have misunderstood what attacked them.
    indonesian: Aku meragukan kesimpulannya. Para tentara mungkin salah memahami apa yang menyerang mereka.
  - key: village.journey.09
    english: An attack from the air could explain why they could not identify the source.
    indonesian: Serangan dari udara bisa menjelaskan kenapa mereka tidak mampu mengenali sumbernya.
  - key: village.journey.10
    english: Or an incendiary weapon, perhaps something similar to a mortar. Fire falling among the trees would look unnatural.
    indonesian: Atau senjata pembakar, mungkin sesuatu yang mirip mortar. Api yang jatuh di antara pepohonan pasti terlihat tidak wajar.
  - key: village.journey.11
    english: But the archive described movement, pursuit, and attacks that changed direction. A mortar cannot hunt people.
    indonesian: Tetapi arsip itu menggambarkan gerakan, pengejaran, dan serangan yang berubah arah. Mortar tidak bisa memburu manusia.
  - key: village.journey.12
    english: Unless terrified survivors connected separate explosions and turned them into a single creature.
    indonesian: Kecuali para penyintas yang ketakutan menghubungkan ledakan terpisah dan menganggapnya sebagai satu makhluk.
  - key: village.journey.13
    english: That still leaves the carbon traces dated to more than six hundred years ago.
    indonesian: Itu masih belum menjelaskan jejak karbon yang diperkirakan berumur lebih dari enam ratus tahun.
  - key: village.journey.14
    english: Those traces prove that something burned there, not that Banaspati caused it.
    indonesian: Jejak itu membuktikan pernah terjadi kebakaran di sana, bukan bahwa Banaspati penyebabnya.
  - key: village.journey.15
    english: True. It could have been a battle, a natural fire, or evidence from several unrelated events.
    indonesian: Benar. Bisa saja itu bekas pertempuran, kebakaran alami, atau jejak dari beberapa kejadian yang tidak berkaitan.
  - key: village.journey.16
    english: The archive may have combined old folklore with a disaster the soldiers could not explain.
    indonesian: Arsip itu mungkin mencampurkan cerita rakyat lama dengan bencana yang tidak dapat dijelaskan para tentara.
  - key: village.journey.17
    english: We should not decide yet. We need testimony from people who know this area and evidence from the forest itself.
    indonesian: Kita belum boleh mengambil kesimpulan. Kita butuh kesaksian warga yang mengenal daerah ini dan bukti dari hutannya sendiri.
  - key: village.journey.18
    english: Then we ask about old stories, routes into Sancang, and anyone who has returned from its interior.
    indonesian: Kalau begitu kita tanyakan cerita lama, jalur masuk ke Sancang, dan siapa pun yang pernah kembali dari pedalamannya.
  - key: village.journey.arrival
    english: We are here. Let us gather information from the villagers. It is already 17:30, but everyone is still busy with their activities.
    indonesian: Kita sudah sampai. Kita cari informasi dari warga. Sudah pukul 17.30, tetapi mereka masih ramai beraktivitas.
